data.text:
China: Circa 1930s. Likely a vintage copy photograph. 32 x 19.5cm.

Chiang Kai-shek, Wade-Giles romanization Chiang Chieh-shih, official name Chiang Chung-cheng, (born October 31, 1887, Fenghua, Zhejiang province, China —died April 5, 1975, Taipei, Taiwan ), soldier and statesman, head of the Nationalist government in China from 1928 to 1949 and subsequently head of the Chinese Nationalist government in exile on Taiwan. Item #51-3884
